# Copy this file to `.env` in this directory (client/.env) and fill in real
# values. Never commit the real `.env` file.
#
# As of this split, the client source (see src/api/client.ts) makes no
# `import.meta.env` calls and requires NO env vars to build or run. All API
# calls are same-origin relative paths (`/api/*`):
#   - In dev, Vite's dev-server proxy (vite.config.ts) forwards `/api/*` to
#     the backend repo's server, currently hardcoded to
#     http://localhost:4000 — update that file if the backend runs
#     elsewhere.
#   - In production, Caddy (in the separate backend repo) reverse-proxies
#     `/api/*` to the Express process and serves this client's static build
#     for everything else.
#
# This file is kept as a placeholder for when/if a real env var (e.g. a
# configurable VITE_API_URL) is introduced — add it here with a name/value
# only, never a real secret.
